reviews.review_text:
Sounds great to me This show gets 5 stars for a few reasons.The sound is in your face and can hear everyone. Was my first show in California. Just perfect way to kick off summer tour.Sunshine friends and fun fun fun. 
 As for the show love the Truckin to end 1st set,so did they is easy to tell.Seems as if they did not want it to end and almost go into Other One a few times towards the end.2nd set is spacey and fun. Love the extra stuff bobby throws in from time to time. Huge fan of 2nd set opening with Playin leaves things wide open for exploring.And explore the boys do with China rider out the playin jam.
 After the show was crazy seems everyone wanted to get there tape on the air ASAP. Was playing everywhere around the campground threw out the night.
Source Info This guy was patched out of Brian Schley's FOB Nak 300 shotgun rig. Same for 7/18/82. Best recordings from these shows (and many others from 1980-1983)

Senn 441's/Marantz 330D Actually I was patched into a set of Sennheiser 441's. Recorded with my old behemoth Marantz Superscope CD330 deck. This was my 1st West Coast Dead Show! I ended up moving to California a year later & then eventually to Ventura. I had travelled out to be with an ex who had moved to Hollywood to be a star. Never saw her in anything so I guess she didn't become one. They let you camp in the parking lot at the beach before they went & paved the whole thing years later. Very dusty but nice to be so close to beach. I remember running out after this show to catch the sunset & thinking this is it the peak of living on the edge & feeling like I'd finally made it in this world. I'm guessing Jeff got the source info wrong because when I first met him I had already upgraded my system to a D6 & a Set of Nak CM300 with the full array of capsules and he assumed that's what I used to record this with.
